The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks in biometrics, specifically for extracting deep features. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the adversarial robustness of these systems, which falls under the category of adversarial attacks and defenses, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) another likely category. The paper also introduces a general technique for forming adversarial examples, which falls under the category of machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category. The paper also discusses the use of distance metrics between gallery templates and extracted deep features, which falls under the category of multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the resilience of systems utilizing deep features compared to end-to-end networks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category.
